#note sweet, a true pre-endgame in the first game of the tournament! I have to bingo and hope that he doesn't bingo back. I saw all the available bingos, but I didn't spot that I could play NONTITLE at 4B instead of 4A. That ends up being my best possible play, winning 7/8 endgames. My choice of NETTLING wings 5/8 (I didn't spot BETATRON over the board due to time constraints). I thought that the other bingos also all won 5/8 (TONALITE, TOILINET) but actually he could have REBIT at N2 for 38 - if I draw the A or O I play out with ZA/ZO for 11, but if I draw the N I get KON/AN for 9 to lose 476-477!
>Edwin_Boama: AEINORT E1 TEN.ORIA +66 504
#note much respect to Edwin, he played a good game and proved to be a strong player throughout the rest of the tournament. As it turns out, even the optimal play of NONTITLE at 4B would've lost given his rack. Exciting game to start the tournament with.
